{
  "stem": "9665.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The other sister married somebody from Antwerp, which was Isaac Feigenbaum, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and-- who had a daughter in 1938 by the name of Paulette.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother married during the war time, but we are coming to that, are we?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't remember my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think they were dead by the time-- when I was around.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there was one uncle who came from Kolomea, and his name was Uncle Schmiel, because whoever came from Poland was poor.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Scheveningen was a very Jewish place because we probably only had a few thousand living there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think 2,000, but I'm not sure about that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we had a lot of people coming from other countries to collect money for themself, or for yeshivas, which were probably also for them because in Poland, people were very poor.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They also came from other places like Czechoslovakia and Bulgaria and Romania to Scheveningen, and Scheveningen by itself was poor, right?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We are talking about the 1930s, right, when there was a depression in the world.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there wasn't much there, really, but they went and, you know, people collected $0.10, $0.25, which for them was a meal, right?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so often they came and they said, we have got 12 children, 14 children at home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So with that little bit of money, which we had, we still gave some away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I'm coming back to what I said before.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father had a good wage, which he collected every month on the first of the month.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we had suppliers of meat and-- not meat, really, chickens.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had three suppliers of chickens, and they needed money at the beginning of the month.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So by the fifth, the sixth, and the seventh, we had to eat chicken.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
